Paper: hep-th/9402085

Date: 1994-02-15

Title: Topological Inflation

Authors: Alexander Vilenkin

Comments: 10 pages

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 72 (1994) 3137-3140

Inflation can occur in the cores of topological defects, where the scalarfield is forced to stay near the maximum of its potential. This topologicalinflation does not require fine-tuning of the initial conditions.